{"TopicId":37474,"ForumId":39,"TopicTitle":"The language of the Kerbals","CreatedByName":"Tophir","CreatedById":58841,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-17T20:07:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Tophir","CreatedById":58841,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-17T20:07:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:underline;\u0022\u003EThe Goal\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe goal is to compile the language of the kerbals. I hope to add roughly 5 words every day so that by this time next year is over there will be roughly 2000 words in the language. I hope to be able to hold a daily vote for a word so there is some input from the community on the creation of the language. \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:underline;\u0022\u003ETodays Vote:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv style=\u0022text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhat will the name of the Kerbal language be: Kerbisk, Kerbad, Kerbilik, or Kerbif\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:underline;\u0022\u003ECurrent List of Words\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:underline;\u0022\u003EPronouns\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI - Kerb\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUs/We - Kerbid\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EYou - Zerb\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHim/Her/It/She/He - Zerban\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThem/They - Zerbonok\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:underline;\u0022\u003EArticles\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA/An - Ik\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe - Iken\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-07-18T04:00:16Z\u0022 title=\u002207/18/2013 04:00  AM\u0022 data-short=\u002210 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 18, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by Tophir\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"buzz66boy","CreatedById":69386,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-17T20:19:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe language spoken by the Kerbals is actually spanish backwards and sped up in the videos fyi, but good luck!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tophir","CreatedById":58841,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-17T20:24:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EFor me speaking Spanish backwards just wasn\u0027t Kerbal enough.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rryy","CreatedById":57357,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-17T20:34:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMaybe there is a language for the \u0022common folk\u0022 of Kerbin and the backwards Spanish for the scientists, engineers, and pilots.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFor the name of the \u0022common\u0022 language, I think \u0022Kerb\u0022 is a good name, even though it isn\u0027t on the list, altough you may have to rename \u0022I\u0022.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-17T20:38:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWelsh. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EJust kidding!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tophir","CreatedById":58841,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-17T20:43:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe reason I have Kerb as I is because it makes a good root word.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Person012345","CreatedById":33728,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-17T20:46:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Eyou could always just make them the same. I mean, \u0022English\u0022 is the word for both the people and the language.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tw1","CreatedById":59717,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-18T14:49:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EIn other things, \u0022Ker\u0022 has been used for \u0022our\u0022\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EKer-bin= our home\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EKer-man= our man\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}